{"cursor":"3155","size":15,"audio":[],"currentlang":"en","article":"'Peter Raymond Grant' and 'Barbara Rosemary Grant', a married couple, are both\nBritish evolutionary biologists at Princeton University; each holds the position\nof Emeritus Professor. They are noted for their work concerning Darwin's finches\non the GalÃ¡pagos Island named Daphne Major. The Grants have spent six months of\nthe year each year since 1973 capturing, tagging, and taking blood samples of\nthe finches on the island.\n\nThe Grants were the subject of the book [[The Beak of the Finch|The Beak of the\nFinch: A Story of Evolution in Our Time]] by Jonathan Weiner (Alfred A. Knopf,\n1994), ISBN 0-679-40003-6, which won the Pulitzer Prize for General Non-Fiction\nin 1995.[http://www.pulitzer.org/year/1995/general-non-fiction/]\n\nIn 2003 the Grants were joint recipients of the Loye and Alden Miller Research\nAward. They won the 2005 Balzan Prize for Population Biology [http://www.balzan-\n.org//premiati.aspx?lang=en&Codice=1117&show=1&from=1117&from1=0]. The Balzan\nPrize citation states:\n:\"Peter and Rosemary Grant are distinguished for their remarkable long-term\n:studies demonstrating evolution in action in GalÃ¡pagos finches. They have\n:demonstrated how very rapid changes in body and beak size in response to\n:changes in the food supply are driven by natural selection. They have also\n:elucidated the mechanisms by which new species arise and how genetic diversity\n:is maintained in natural populations. The work of the Grants has had a seminal\n:influence in the fields of population biology, evolution and ecology.\"\n\nPeter was made a Fellow of the Royal Society in 1987 and Rosemary in 2007. In\n2008 both Peter and Rosemary Grant were among the thirteen recipients of the Darwin-\nWallace Medal, which is bestowed every 50 years by the Linnean Society of\nLondon. In 2009 they were recipients of the annual Kyoto Prize in basic\nsciences, an international award honoring significant contributions to the\nscientific, cultural and spiritual betterment of mankind.\n","linknr":110,"url":"Peter_and_Rosemary_Grant","recorded":1376427532,"links":["/w/index.php?title=Peter_and_Rosemary_Grant&action=edit","/w/index.php?title=Peter_and_Rosemary_Grant&action=edit","//bits.wikimedia.org/favicon/wikipedia.ico","/w/opensearch_desc.php","//en.wikipedia.org/w/api.php?action=rsd","//creativecommons.org/licenses/by-sa/3.0/","/w/index.php?title=Special:RecentChanges&feed=atom","http://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Peter_and_Rosemary_Grant","//bits.wikimedia.org/en.wikipedia.org/load.php?debug=false&lang=en&modules=ext.gadget.DRN-wizard%2CReferenceTooltips%2Ccharinsert%2Cteahouse%7Cext.rtlcite%2Cwikihiero%7Cext.uls.nojs%7Cmediawiki.legacy.commonPrint%2Cshared%7Cmw.PopUpMediaTransform%7Cskins.vector&only=styles&skin=vector&*","//bits.wikimedia.org/en.wikipedia.org/load.php?debug=false&lang=en&modules=ext.visualEditor.viewPageTarget.noscript&only=styles&skin=vector&*","//bits.wikimedia.org/en.wikipedia.org/load.php?debug=false&lang=en&modules=site&only=styles&skin=vector&*","//bits.wikimedia.org/en.wikipedia.org/load.php?debug=false&lang=en&modules=startup&only=scripts&skin=vector&*","//bits.wikimedia.org/geoiplookup","//meta.wikimedia.org","#mw-navigation","#p-search","/wiki/United_Kingdom","/wiki/Evolutionary_biology","/wiki/Princeton_University","/wiki/Darwin%27s_finches","/wiki/Gal%C3%A1pagos_Islands","/wiki/Daphne_Major","/wiki/The_Beak_of_the_Finch","/wiki/Jonathan_Weiner","/wiki/Special:BookSources/0679400036","/wiki/Pulitzer_Prize","http://www.pulitzer.org/year/1995/general-non-fiction/","/wiki/Loye_and_Alden_Miller_Research_Award","/wiki/Balzan_Prize","http://www.balzan.org//premiati.aspx?lang=en&Codice=1117&show=1&from=1117&from1=0","/wiki/Fellow_of_the_Royal_Society","/wiki/Darwin-Wallace_Medal","/wiki/Linnean_Society_of_London","/wiki/Kyoto_Prize","/w/index.php?title=Peter_and_Rosemary_Grant&action=edit&section=1","/w/index.php?title=Peter_and_Rosemary_Grant&veaction=edit